UC Berkeley - Tau PET PVC 6mm Res analysis

Source: R/data.R
UCBERKELEY_TAUPVC_6MM.Rd

UC Berkeley - Tau PET PVC 6mm Res analysis data. More information is available at https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Usage

data(UCBERKELEY_TAUPVC_6MM)

Format

A data frame with 1811 observations and 335 variables.

Source

https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Details

  • ORIGPROT character Original study protocol , with options: ADNI1, ADNIGO, ADNI2, ADNI3, ADNI4

  • LONIUID character LONI Image ID

  • RID numeric Participant roster ID (unique participant identifier that should be used to merge data) Range value: 21, ..., 10340

  • VISCODE character Visit code

  • SITEID numeric Site ID Range value: 2, ..., 941

  • PTID character ADNI Participant ID consisting of 3-digit "SITEID" and 4-digit "RID"

  • SCANDATE Date SCAN acquisition date Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • PROCESSDATE Date Date quantification pipeline was run Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • TRACER character PET Radiotracer , with options: FTP, MK6240

  • TRACER_SUVR_WARNING character Reminder of the incomparability of SUVRs from different tracers. See UCBERKELEY Tau Processing Methods PDF. , with options: DO NOT COMPARE SUVRs ACROSS TRACERS

  • META_TEMPORAL_SUVR numeric Weighted mean SUVR of Jack et al temporal meta-ROI. All SUVRs in this file are normalized to the inferior cerebellar grey matter unless otherwise noted. See UCBERKELEY Tau PET Processing Methods PDF on LONI for details. Range value: 0.625, ..., 7.089

  • META_TEMPORAL_VOLUME numeric Jack et al temporal meta-ROI size in mm^3 Range value: 36639, ..., 97274

  • CTX_ENTORHINAL_SUVR numeric ctx-bilateral-entorhinal Range value: 0.729, ..., 5.592

  • CTX_ENTORHINAL_VOLUME numeric ctx-bilateral-entorhinal ROI size in mm^3 Range value: 746, ..., 5946
